MooseX::Role::UserDaemon Version 0.05

DESCRIPTION

A moose role ment to simplify writing of perl daemons and scripts
running as a normal user. It implements:
  1. A lockfile to ensure only one running instace at any given time.
  2. A pidfile to we can find the running process id if we need to signal it.
  3. Daemonize with double forking for running processes in the background

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc MooseX::Role::UserDaemon

